    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically sound 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2). This wide-body variant features the naturally aspirated 3.6L flat-six M96 powerplant, delivering linear torque through a 6-speed manual transaxle and a sophisticated viscous coupling AWD system. Critical preventative maintenance is complete, including a dual-row ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a recent water pump replacement. The chassis retains its precision with Bilstein B6 dampers and refreshed control arm bushings. While the Arctic Silver finish shows minor road-going patina, the internals are dialed in, featuring a dry rear main seal and a clean DME report. Riding on staggered factory 'Turbo-twist' alloys wrapped in fresh Michelin Pilot Sport 4S rubber, this C4S is engineered for the purist seeking a driver-focused 911 with a sorted drivetrain.",
